The Software as a Medical Device (SaMD) market is expected to witness significant growth leading up to 2031. Factors such as the increasing focus on remote patient monitoring, advancements in technology, and the rising demand for healthcare solutions are driving this growth. The standalone software segment is anticipated to dominate the market, fueled by the convenience it offers in terms of diagnostics, personalized treatment, and monitoring. In terms of application, the diagnosis segment is projected to hold a substantial market share, driven by the increasing prevalence of chronic diseases and the need for accurate and efficient diagnostic tools. Among end users, hospitals are expected to be the key adopters of SaMD due to the growing burden of patient data management and the need for streamlined healthcare processes.

